113
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,440
7:30 PM.

114
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:44,060
7:30 PM?

115
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:44,880
-Yeah.
-Got it.

116
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:48,880
Director Wei is going as well?

117
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,430
Yeah.

118
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,200
It’s a reunion party

119
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:50,860
of my medical schoolmates.

120
00:07:51,490 --> 00:07:52,000
I’ll wait for you

121
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:52,960
at the parking lot after work.

122
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,320
OK, I’ll go. Don’t worry.

123
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,120
Let’s go.

124
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:03,240
Director Shao,

125
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,240
do you often hold parties

126
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,200
where neurologists

127
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:08,560
talk about cases?

128
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,080
We’re just friends.

129
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,160
It’s just a casual gathering.

130
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,200
You talk about

131
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,800
professional stuff, though, don’t you?

132
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:15,920
I wish I could learn something

133
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,640
from you at a party like this.

134
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,480
I may invite you in the future.

135
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,480
Your dressing is changed.

136
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,560
I’m going to work.

137
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,030
Alright, bye-bye.

138
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:33,840
Bye-bye.

139
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,200
He plays favorites.

140
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:40,240
Mi Ka was unqualified for last surgery.

141
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:41,360
But he asked Mi Ka there.

142
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,360
Director Shao always leaves the

143
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,790
best opportunities to Mi Ka.

144
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,600
Not really.

145
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,000
Other doctors also get opportunities.

146
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:46,720
Look…

147
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,200
You’re making a big deal out of it.

148
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,400
This is different.

149
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:50,680
It’s a private party.

150
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,160
All the elites and experts
will be there.

151
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,520
A resident doctor never gets such

152
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:54,520
a great opportunity.

153
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,640
Mi Ka is the first one who gets it.

154
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,400
He said he’d invite you in the future.

155
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,840
Just chill.

156
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:04,200
Sister.

157
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,520
Dinner?

158
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:13,080
Mi Ka,

159
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,160
allow me to introduce.

160
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,160
This is Yi Qian,

161
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,440
a classmate of Dr. Shao.

162
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:17,000
The three of us all

163
00:09:17,010 --> 00:09:17,840
graduated from the same school.

164
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:18,680
Nice to meet you, Mr. Yi.

165
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:19,800
Nice to meet you, too.

166
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,320
I’m not as formal as Dr. Shao

167
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,040
and this isn’t working hour.

168
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:24,760
Thanks.

169
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:26,160
You’re welcome. Please enjoy.

170
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,960
Are all special police officers

171
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,280
very cool?

172
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,200
Do you just knock down

173
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:31,920
bad guys

174
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,960
pretty much effortlessly?

175
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:35,720
Not really.

176
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:36,920
Sometimes, we’d

177
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,160
hide in a bin or something.

178
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,040
Uh,

179
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,040
she just came back from abroad.

180
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,600
She studies art.

181
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:50,720
She doesn’t know much

182
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:51,640
about the work of special police.

183
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,400
Is there a particular
painter that you like?

184
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,120
No.

185
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:54,840
Gustav Klimt

186
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,080
is my favorite painter.

187
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,520
I just went to his art show

188
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,320
in Austria not long ago.

189
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:02,960
Uh, how about

190
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:05,760
artists? Anyone?

191
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:11,840
No one.

192
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,040
No time for them.

193
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,080
Um,

194
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,560
let’s eat.

195
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:20,560
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

196
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:21,920
Just, just tuck in.

197
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:23,720
Dinner, finally.

198
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,680
Tuck in, tuck in.

199
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:40,520
Let’s begin.

200
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:41,840
Let’s begin, Shao.

201
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:44,300
(Case briefing)

202
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,720
This is the dinner you
wanted to have with me?

203
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:14,200
You, me, dinner.

204
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,120
Anything wrong?

205
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,040
Come on.

206
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,880
This is pretty awkward, don’t you think?

207
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:20,920
You’ll get to know each other over time.

208
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:21,920
You’re both adults.

209
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,480
What do you mean, awkward?

210
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,800
But the girl

211
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,480
was talking about some Klimt guy.

212
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,080
She and I aren’t even
living in the same world.

213
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,280
Xing Kelei,

214
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,920
who lives in the same world
with you, then?

215
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:35,760
The person who

216
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:37,520
lives next door, right?

217
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,600
How do you know?

218
00:11:40,880 --> 00:11:42,480
Do you take me for a fool?

219
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,600
Why did you take

220
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:44,800
so many of my facial masks?

221
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,120
Listen,

222
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:49,760
I came back with a task on me.

223
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:50,960
Mom said

224
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,920
either one of us must get married.

225
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,720
If not,

226
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,680
she’ll come back and personally

227
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,200
see to it.

228
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:01,080
You get married, then.

229
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,520
You’re old anyway.

230
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,000
Fine.

231
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:11,080
I’m old. I get married first.

232
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,840
Then I have a baby.

233
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:13,960
You resign

234
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,640
and be the manager of the company.

235
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:17,840
Sister,

236
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:19,400
come on.

237
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,040
How about this?

238
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,680
We work together against mom.

239
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,240
Do you think she’s

240
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,800
an idiot?

241
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,000
Thanks, Director Shao. Thanks.

242
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:43,520
See you.

243
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,080
See you.

244
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:07,240
Uh, I...

245
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,760
Shut up.

246
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:10,600
Hello.

247
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,520
Oh, look at the clothes steamer.

248
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,800
It looks quite familiar.

249
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,400
Here are

250
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:31,800
my facial masks.

251
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:35,440
No wonder.

252
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,160
I thought my stuff

253
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,040
had their own will

254
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,800
and started running around

255
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,720
by themselves.

256
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,280
Look at me, Xing Kelei.

257
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:48,240
So?

258
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,240
Are you happy with the house?

259
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:52,760
It’s OK. Just...

260
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,080
-I’m not asking you.
-In winter, it...

261
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,080
Y-Yeah.

262
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:01,720
One of my colleagues
knows Instructor Xing

263
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,800
and told me about the house for rent.

264
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,440
Uh, only one room,

265
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:08,600
other rooms are not for rent.

266
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,120
It’s close to

267
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,240
the hospital that I work in

268
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:13,760
and the rent is reasonable,

269
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:14,800
so, I took the room.

270
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:15,800
When I took the room,

271
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:16,360
I didn’t know

272
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,200
it was Instructor Xing’s house.

273
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,880
Let me introduce myself.

274
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:22,600
I’m

275
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,960
Xing Kelei’s

276
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,680
sister, Xing Keyao.

277
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:33,120
Hi.

278
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,160
Mi Ka, right?

279
00:14:35,490 --> 00:14:36,000
Xing Kelei told me

280
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,200
that you rented one room

281
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,640
in his house

282
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:40,240
and that he was your instructor.

283
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,560
You’re doctor, correct?

284
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:43,320
I, too, studied medicine.

285
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,040
I didn’t become a doctor

286
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,240
because I needed to help
with our family business.

287
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,040
If you need anything

288
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,520
from me,

289
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:51,040
just let me know.

290
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,480
I’m your neighbor.

291
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:57,720
OK.

292
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:58,840
